The paper deals with the analysis of cooperative relaying in wireless networks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The presence of interference is a common issue in wireless networks, which makes the paper relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. The use of Rayleigh and Nakagami-m fading channels also suggests a possible connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and communication (cs.COM) sub-categories.
